,'[]','[\'Syntax\', \'Example\', \'Example\', \'Example\']','[]','[]','[\'In HTML, the <html> element is always the root element. Although the :root is equivalent to html selector because both of them target the same element, but the :root selector has a higher specificity.\', \"Now, let\'s try html selector and :root selector simultaneously. Although they both work similar but in the matter of specificity, the :root selector wins.\"]','[\'In this example, we are going to define the same properties in html selector as well as in :root selector. The properties in :root selector will work because of higher specificity. But those properties that are not in :root selector but mentioned in html selector, then the properties of html selector will work.\', \'In the above example, we can see that the background-color and color properties are both mentioned in html as well as in :root selector, but in the output, the properties mentioned in :root selector will work. This is because of the higher specificity of the :root selector.\']','[\':root {\', \'<!DOCTYPE html>\', \'<html>\', \'<head>\', \'<title>:root selector</title>\', \'<style>\', \':root {\', \'background: lightblue;\', \'color: blue;\', \'text-align: center;\', \'</style>\', \'</head>\', \'<body>\', \'<h1>Welcome to the javaTpoint.com</h1>\', \'<h2>This is an example of :root selector</h2>\', \'</body>\', \'</html>\', \'<!DOCTYPE html>\', \'<html>\', \'<head>\', \'<title>:root selector</title>\', \'<style>\', \':root {\', \'background-color: lightblue;\', \'color: blue;\', \'text-align: center;\', \'background-color: red;\', \'color: white;\', \'font-size: 30px;\', \'</style>\', \'</head>\', \'<body>\', \'<h1>Welcome to the javaTpoint.com</h1>\', \'<h2>This is an example of :root selector and html selector</h2>\', \'</body>\', \'</html>\']','[]','[]','[]'),(61,'[\'CSS Specificity\']','[\'When more than one conflicting rules of CSS indicates the same element, then the browser will follow some rules for determining 