xample\', \'Example2- use of mix units\', \'Example3- nested calc() function\']','[]','[\'It is a powerful CSS concept because it allows us to mix any units, such as percentage and pixel.\', \'The result of the expression will be treated as the value of the property, so, the value of width will be 75% and the value of height will be 275px.\', \'Now, we will see another demonstration in which we use mixed units.\', \"Let\'s see another example in which we will use nested calc() function.\"]','[\'This CSS function takes a single parameter expression, and the result of this mathematical expression will be used as a value. It can be any simple expression using the four arithmetic operators (+, -, *, /). The expression is mandatory to define.\', \'In this example, we are using the calc() function to define the width and height of the div element. There is the subtraction in the expression of calc() function with same units.\', \'In the above example, we can directly mention the values of height and width. Although the expression in the above example has the same units, what happens when the units are different, then it will be hard to write the values directly.\']','[]','[\'calc( Expression );\', \'<!DOCTYPE html>\', \'<html>\', \'<head>\', \'<title> calc() function </title>\', \'<style>\', \'.jtp {\', \'width: calc(150% - 75%);\', \'height: calc(350px - 75px);\', \'background-color: lightblue;\', \'padding-top: 50px;\', \'}\', \'.jtp1 {\', \'font-size: 30px;\', \'font-weight: bold;\', \'color: blue;\', \'}\', \'h1 {\', \'color: blue;\', \'}\', \'color: green;\', \'</style>\', \'</head>\', \'<body>\', \'<center>\', \'<div class = \"jtp\">\', \'<div class = \"jtp1\"> Welcome to the javaTpoint.com </div>\', \'<h1> This is an example of calc() Function </h1>\', \'<h2> width: calc(150% - 75%);  </h2>\', \'<h2> height: calc(350px - 75px); </h2>\', \'</div>\', \'</center>\', \'</body>\', \'</html>\', \'<!DOCTYPE html>\', \'<html>\', \'<head>\', \'<title> calc() function </title>\', \'<style>\', \'.jtp {\', \'width: calc(40% + 10em);\', \'height: calc(350px + 75px);\', \'background-color: lightblue;\', \'padding-top: calc(10% - 10px);\', \'padding-left: calc(10% + 10px);\', \'}\', \'.jtp1 {\', \'font-size: 30px;\', \'font-weight: bold;\', \'color: blue;\', \'}\', \'h1 {\', \'color: blue;\', \'}\', \'color: green;\', \'</style>\', \'</head>\', \'<body>\', \'<div class = \"jtp\">\', \'<div class = \"jtp1\"> Welcome to the javaTpoint.com </div>\', \'<h1> This is an example of calc() Function </h1>\', \'<h2> width: calc(40% + 10em); </h2>\', \'<h2> height: calc(350px + 75px); </h2>\', \'<h2> padding-top: calc(10% - 10px); </h2>\', \'<h2> padding-left: calc(10% + 10px); </h2>\', \'</div>\', \'</body>\', \'</html>\', \'<!DOCTYPE html>\', \'<html>\', \'<head>\', \'<title> calc() function </title>\', \'<style>\', \'.jtp {\', \'width: calc( calc(40em / 3) * 2);\', \'height: calc(350px + 75px);\', \'background-color: lightblue;\', \'}\', \'.jtp1 {\', \'font-size: 30px;\', \'font-weight: bold;\', \'color: blue;\', \'}\', \'h1 {\', \'color: blue;\', \'}\', \'color: green;\', \'</style>\', \'</head>\', \'<body>\', \'<div class = \"jtp\">\', \'<div class = \"jtp1\"> Welcome to the javaTpoint.com </div>\', \'<h1> This is an example of nested calc() Function </h1>\', \'<h2> width: calc( calc(40em / 3) * 2); </h2>\', \'<h2> height: calc(350px + 75px); </h2>\', \'</div>\', \'</body>\', \'</html>\']','[]','[]','[]'),(68,'[\'CSS Clip\']','[\'This CSS property specifies the visible area of an element. It applies to absolutely positioned elements (position: absolute;). It is generally used when the image is larger than its containing element.\']','[\'https://www.javatpoint.com/css-clip-path\', \'https://www.javatpoint.com/css-calc\', \'https://www.javatpoint.com/https://www.javatpoint.com/oprweb/test.jsp?filename=CSSClip1\', \'https://www.javatpoint.com/https://www.javatpoint.com/oprweb/test.jsp?filename=CSSClip2\', \'https://www.javatpoint.com/css-clip-path\', \'https://www.javatpoint.com/css-calc\', \'https://www.javatpoint.com/css-clip-path\']','[]','[]','[]','[\'Syntax\', \'Possible values\', \'Example\', \'Example\']','[]','[\'It allows us to define a rectangle, which is specified as four coordinates for clipping an absolutely positioned element.\', \'auto: It is the default value that shows the element as it is. There will be no clipping.\', \'shape: It is used to clip an element. It clips the defined area of the element. Its valid value is rect(top, right, bottom, left).\']','[]','[]','[\'clip: auto | shape | initial | inherit;\', \'<!DOCTYPE html>\', \'<html>\', \'<head>\', \'<style>\', \'.auto {\', \'position: absolute;\', \'width: 400px;\', \'height: 400px;\', \'clip: auto;\', \'}\', \'\', \'</style>\', \'</head>\', \'<body>\', \'<h2>clip: auto; property</h2>\', \'<img src= \"jtp.png\" class=\"auto\">\', \'</body>\', \'</html>\', \'<head>\', \'<style type = \"text/css\">\', \'div {\', \'background: url(jtp.png);\', \'clip: rect(0px, 150px, 250px, 0px);\', \'border:3px solid red;\', \'height:200px;\', \'width: 250px;\', \'position: absolute;\', \'}\', \'</style>\', \'</head>\', \'<body>\', \'<div></div>\', \'</body>\', \'</html>\']','[]','[]','[]'),(69,'[\'CSS clip-path\']','[\"This CSS property is used to create a clipping region and specifies the element\'s area that should be visible. The area inside the region will be visible, while the outside area is hidden. Anything outside the clipping will be clipped by browsers, including borders, text-shadows, and many more.\"]','[\'https://www.javatpoint.com/css-background-blend-mode\', \'https://www.javatpoint.com/css-clip\', \'https://www.javatpoint.com/https://www.javatpoint.com/css-text-shadow\', \'https://www.javatpoint.com/https://www.javatpoint.com/css-tutorial\', \'https://www.javatpoint.com/https://www.javatpoint.com/oprweb/test.jsp?filename=css-clip-path1\', \'https://www.javatpoint.com/https://www.javatpoint.com/oprweb/test.jsp?filename=css-clip-path2\', \