n element.\', \'In the above output, we can see the resizing of div element in the horizontal direction. We can see the triangular knob at the bottom right corner of the element. To see the effect, we have to click and drag the knob.\', \'In the above output, we can see the resizing of div element in the vertical direction. We can see a triangular knob at the bottom right corner of the element. To see the effect, we have to click and drag the knob.\']','[\"This CSS property is used to define how an element is resizable by the user. It doesn\'t apply on the block or inline elements where overflow is set to visible. So, to control the resizing of an element, we have to set the overflow other than visible like (overflow: hidden or overflow: scroll).\", \'It is possible to resize the elements either in a horizontal or vertical direction or in both directions. After applying the resize property to an element, we can see a small triangular knob at the bottom right corner of the element. The user can drag the knob to enlarge the textarea in either vertical, horizontal, or in both directions.\']','[\'resize: none | horizontal | vertical | both | initial | inherit;\', \'<!DOCTYPE html>\', \'<style>\', \'border: 2px solid red;\', \'padding: 20px;\', \'font-size: 25px;\', \'width: 300px;\', \'resize: horizontal;\', \'overflow: auto;\', \'background-color: lightgreen;\', \'color: blue;\', \'</style>\', \'</head>\', \'<center>\', \'<h1>Example of the resize: horizontal; </h1>\', \'<p> This is the div element. </p>\', \'<p> To see the resizing effect, click and drag the bottom right corner of this div element. </p>\', \'</center>\', \'</body>\', \'</html>\', \'<!DOCTYPE html>\', \'<style>\', \'border: 2px solid red;\', \'padding: 20px;\', \'font-size: 25px;\', \'width: 300px;\', \'resize: vertical;\', \'overflow: auto;\', \'background-color: lightgreen;\', \'color: blue;\', \'</style>\', \'</head>\', \'<center>\', \'<h1>Example of the resize: vertical; </h1>\', \'<p> This is the 